reviews.review_text:
the strangest of places This Scarlet > Fire is incredible. It's one of my favorites! The band always kicked it up a few notches in Indiana for some reason. Maybe they just loved to blow the minds of the local Hoosiers! It worked on me! This audience tape sounds really good. The cymbals come in clear, and Phil sounds good. Donna is singing her heart out like she never wants to leave the band. This tour has some great high points. Jerry, in particular, is on his A game most of this tour. I feel these last few dates with Keith and Donna are very overlooked and it would be cool to see an official release from a January 79 show! 
4/5 overall. 5/5 for the Scarlet > Fire and China > Rider.
